  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 space-y-12">
    {/* Header */}
    <div class="text-center space-y-6">
      <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-green-700 font-primary">
        Offer a Helping Hand this Ramadan 2025
      </h3>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto font-roboto">
        Support Those in Need this Ramadan 2025 and Create a Lasting Impact.
      </p>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center">
          <div class="w-full border-t"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative flex justify-center">
          <div
            class="h-2 w-64 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-400 via-red-500 to-red-400 rounded-full"
          >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Content Grid with Divider */}
    <div class="relative">
      {/* Vertical Divider Line */}
      <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 hidden md:block">
        <div
          class="h-full w-1 bg-green-600 rounded-full transform -translate-x-1/2"
        >
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        {/* Left Column */}
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none md:pl-6 md:pr-8">
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto">
              Ramadan 2025 is a time eagerly awaited by Muslims around the world
              each year. It is a period of devotion, mercy, and drawing closer
              to Allah (SWT). This sacred time offers an opportunity to seek
              forgiveness, reflect on our blessings, and assist those in need.
              It reminds us of how fortunate we are and helps us understand the
              struggles faced by those in impoverished communities, such as in
              Syria, Pakistan, Palestine, Yemen, and The Gambia.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto mt-6">
              You can support our Ramadan Appeal by donating your Zakat to those
              who need it most. While many of us fast during the daylight hours,
              for millions worldwide, hunger is a daily reality. Countless
              people lack food for iftar and continue to suffer from hunger. The
              COVID-19 pandemic has worsened this crisis, leaving even more
              without enough to eat. Every day, around 795 million people go
              hungry, unsure of when they will eat next, many suffering from
              malnutrition and lacking the essential nutrients needed for
              survival.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Right Column */}
        <div class="space-y-6 md:pl-8">
          <div
            class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-600 relative"
          >
            <p class="text-green-800 font-bold text-lg italic">
              The Prophet (saw) said that "Whoever observes fasts during the
              month of Ramadan out of sincere faith, and hoping to attain
              Allah's rewards, then all his past sins will be forgiven."
              [Bukhari]
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto">
              This Ramadan 2025, consider donating your Zakat to our Ramadan
              Appeal. Zakat is an obligation for every adult, sane Muslim who
              possesses wealth above a certain threshold. It involves giving
              2.5% of your wealth to those in need. Your Zakat can save lives,
              provide essentials like clean water, food, shelter, education, and
              healthcare, and help families escape poverty.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto mt-6">
              During Ramadan, good deeds are greatly rewarded. Allah (SWT)
              multiplies acts of kindness seventy fold. Your donations this
              Ramadan can make a significant impact, helping entire communities
              rise out of poverty and offering long-term solutions to hunger and
              hardship.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SliderNew
    img1="/images/ramadan/ramadan-slider-1.JPG"
    img2="/images/ramadan/ramadan-slider-2.JPG"
    img3="/images/ramadan/ramadan-slider-3.jpeg"
    img4="/images/ramadan/ramadan-slider-4.jpg"
    img5="/images/ramadan/ramadan-slider-5.jpg"
  />

  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 md:py-12 space-y-12">
    {/* Header */}
    <div class="text-center space-y-6">
      <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-green-700 font-primary">
        Spread happiness this ramadan
      </h3>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto font-roboto">
        Share the blessings of Ramadan by providing food, hope, and relief to
        families in desperate need.
      </p>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center">
          <div class="w-full border-t border-gray-200"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative flex justify-center">
          <div
            class="h-2 w-64 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-400 via-red-500 to-red-400 rounded-full"
          >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Content Grid with Divider */}
    <div class="relative">
      {/* Vertical Divider Line */}
      <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 hidden md:block">
        <div
          class="h-full w-1 bg-green-600 rounded-full transform -translate-x-1/2"
        >
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        {/* Left Column */}
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none md:pl-6 md:pr-8">
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto">
              As we gather with our families for iftar this Ramadan 2025,
              millions across the uk and the world will have nothing to break
              their fast with. For struggling families, widows, and orphans,
              Ramadan 2025 is not just a test of faith but a daily battle
              against hunger and hardship. The month of mercy is a time to
              reflect, give Zakat in Ramadan, and extend a helping hand to those
              who need it the most.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto mt-6">
              At Edhi Foundation, we are committed to ensuring no one is left
              behind through our Ramadan Appeal 2025. Together, we will provide
              essential food packs, hot iftar meals, and vital aid to low income
              families and the children who lost their parents. Your support can
              bring comfort to poor families, vulnerable children, and those
              living in intense poverty. A single ramadan donation can provide a
              warm meal for someone. <br /><br /> Don't miss the opportunity to give
              and earn endless rewards in this blessed month of Ramadan 2025. With
              Your Ramadan donation, vulnerable families can rebuild their lives,
              find stability, and embrace a future filled with dignity, hope, and
              opportunity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Right Column */}
        <div class="space-y-6 md:pl-8">
          <div
            class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-600 relative"
          >
            <p class="text-green-800 font-bold text-lg italic">
              As the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) said: “The best
              charity is that given in Ramadan.” This hadith emphasizes that the
              rewards of charitable giving are multiplied during this holy
              month.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto">
              In last Ramadan, with the help of our donors, we provided
              thousands of meals to families who face hunger and crisis. This
              year, the need is even greater. By donating your Zakat in Ramadan,
              Sadaqah, or Fidyah, you can become a source of relief for those
              struggling with their life. Every meal given, every package
              delivered, and every act of kindness brings hope to those facing
              unimaginable hardship in this ramadan 2025.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed font-roboto mt-6">
              Let our Ramadan Appeal 2025 be a time of generosity and positive
              impact across the uk and all over globe. Help us nourish lives,
              spread happiness, restore dignity, and bring joy to those in
              urgent need. Together, we can make this Ramadan 2025 one of ease
              and blessings for the less fortunate. Donate now and be the reason
              someone smiles this Ramadan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="text-center md:pt-26 pt-12">
    <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </p>
    <h6>
      Explore our FAQs for clear insights on giving, eligibility, and the
      positive impact <br /> your contribution can make in transforming lives.
    </h6>
  </section>
  <section class="px-6 md:py-20 py-10 mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <div
        class="faq-item border border-green-400 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden hover:border-green-300 transition-colors"
      >
        <button
          class="faq-button w-full px-6 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-between text-gray-900"
        >
          <span class="text-lg font-medium"
            >When does Ramadan 2025 start and end?</span
          >
          <span class="icon-plus text-gray-400 text-2xl font-thin">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer border-t border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Ramadan 2025 is expected to begin on the evening of Friday, Feb 28,
            2025, and end on the evening of Sunday, March 30, 2025. The exact
            dates may vary depending on the moon sighting in different regions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div
        class="faq-item border border-green-400 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden hover:border-green-300 transition-colors"
      >
        <button
          class="faq-button w-full px-6 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-between text-gray-900"
        >
          <span class="text-lg font-medium"
            >When is Laylat al-Qadr in Ramadan 2025?</span
          >
          <span class="icon-plus text-gray-400 text-2xl font-thin">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer border-t border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Laylat al-Qadr, known as the "Night of Power," is anticipated to
            occur during the last 10 days of Ramadan, likely on March 26th,
            2025. It holds great spiritual importance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div
        class="faq-item border border-green-400 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden hover:border-green-300 transition-colors"
      >
        <button
          class="faq-button w-full px-6 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-between text-gray-900"
        >
          <span class="text-lg font-medium"
            >How can I use a Ramadan timetable effectively?</span
          >
          <span class="icon-plus text-gray-400 text-2xl font-thin">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer border-t border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            A Ramadan timetable offers precise Suhoor and Iftar times, ensuring
            Muslims observe their fasts correctly. It also marks important
            dates, like Laylat al-Qadr, to enhance worship during Ramadan.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div
        class="faq-item border border-green-400 rounded-lg bg-white overflow-hidden hover:border-green-300 transition-colors"
      >
        <button
          class="faq-button w-full px-6 py-4 text-left hover:bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-between text-gray-900"
        >
          <span class="text-lg font-medium"
            >How do prayer times differ during Ramadan across cities?</span
          >
          <span class="icon-plus text-gray-400 text-2xl font-thin">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer border-t border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Prayer times, Suhoor (pre-dawn meal), and Iftar (breaking fast) vary
            by location. A local Ramadan timetable ensures Muslims follow the
            correct timings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
